Multiple assignments to the same variable does not provide any spacing to match up with each iteration.
For example:
void Foo()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
    {
        int x = 6;
        x = 7;
    }
}

Foo();
Shows
| i     | x     | 
| 0     | 6     | 
| 1     | 7     | 
| 2     | 6     | 
|       | 7     | 
When it should show:
| i     | x     | 
| 0     | 6     | 
|       | 7     | 
| 1     | 6     | 
|       | 7     | 
| 2     |       |

