I have configured the Defects4j on my 14.04 Ubuntu as indicated in the Defects4j README.md. My Java version 1.7.0_80 and I also set the TZ environment successfully.
Then I downloaded the buggy program named as Chart_5 on my Ubuntu. When I opened the terminal in the folder of Chart_5 program and executed:"defects4j export -p tests.trigger", the output was as follow:
Running ant (export.tests.trigger)......................................... OK
org.jfree.data.xy.junit.XYSeriesTests::testBug1955483
However, when I executed:"defects4j test" in the same folder, the printed information was:
Running ant (compile.tests)................................................ OK
Running ant (run.dev.tests)................................................ OK
Failing tests: 2
org.jfree.data.time.junit.MonthTests::testParseMonth
org.jfree.data.xy.junit.XYSeriesTests::testBug1955483
It was really out of my expectation that I got extra failing test named "org.jfree.data.time.junit.MonthTests::testParseMonth". To figure out this, I studied the files including Chart_5/tests/org/jfree/data/time/junit/MonthTests.java, Chart_5/source/org/jfree/data/time/Month.java and the failing_tests file in the root folder of Chart_5. After that I found that it is the code in MonthTests.java:
""""
// test 3...
try {
month = Month.parseMonth("March 1993");
}
catch (TimePeriodFormatException e) {
month = new Month(1, 1900);
}
assertEquals(3, month.getMonth());
assertEquals(1993, month.getYear().getYear());
""""
that triggers the failure of Month.java.
So is it a bug which is omitted by Defects4j file?
I mean, in the file produced by Defect4j, only one failing test is recorded. But when I run the buggy program Chart_5 I have got two failing tests. So could anyone offer some help or guidance? Thanks a lot.

